# Urnyak, Chekmagushevsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Urnyak (; , Ürnäk) is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative centre of Urnyaksky Selsoviet, Chekmagushevsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 665 as of 2010. There are 10 streets.
Geography
Urnyak is located 15&nbsp;km southeast of Chekmagush (the district's administrative centre) by road. Nur is the nearest rural locality.
